Health Authorities Act
Hospital Transfer Regulation
[Last amended March 6, 2024 by B.C. Reg. 42/2024]

Transfer of assets and liabilities
1  The assets and liabilities of a society that has been designated as a hospital under the Hospital Act may be transferred to a board or council by

(a)the society agreeing to the transfer by special resolution as defined in section 1 of the Societies Act, and

(b)the board or council agreeing to assume the assets and liabilities by bylaw passed by a majority of not less than 75% of the votes of the members of the board or council by voting personally or by proxy after receiving at least 14 days' notice of the proposed bylaw.

[am. B.C. Regs. 211/2015, s. 23; 42/2024, Sch. 1, s. 19.]

[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: Health Authorities Act, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 180, s. 21 (2).]
